fredr
  • Reference

Send a request to the FRED API server

Send a request to the FRED API server

fredr(endpoint, ..., to_frame = TRUE, print_req = FALSE)

Arguments

endpoint

A string representing the FRED API path of interest. See https://api.stlouisfed.org/docs/fred/.
...

A series of paramters to be used in the query. Of the form param_key = 'param_value'. Acceptable parameters are specific to the API path. See https://api.stlouisfed.org/docs/fred/.
to_frame

A boolean value indicating whether or not the response should be parsed and formatted as a tbl_df. Default is TRUE.
print_req

A boolean value indicating whether or not the request should be printed as well. Useful for debugging.

Value

A tbl_df. If to_frame is TRUE, return is a reponse object from httr::GET().

Examples

 fredr("series/observations",
       series_id = "GNPCA",
       observation_start = "1990-01-01",
       observation_end = "2000-01-01")
